{
  "text": "Thank you very much. I don't wish to take up extra time by asking questions over again. Some are so important I try to ask some similar questions in different ways to expand on the answer. Seems to be what we're getting at, maybe not. In the book Oahspe it states that if an individual is more than fifty percent for others— that is, goes over the 50% service to others, and is less than fifty percent for service to self, then he is harvestable. Is this a correct statement? I am Ra. This is correct if the harvesting is to be for the positive fourth dimensional level.",
